content.p:
Reaffirms the obligation of States to ensure that persons belonging to national or ethnic, religious and linguistic minorities may exercise fully and effectively all human rights and fundamental freedoms without any discrimination and in full equality before the law, as proclaimed in the Declaration on the Rights of Persons Belonging to National or Ethnic, Religious and Linguistic Minorities,
Resolution 47/135, annex. and draws attention to the relevant provisions of the Durban Declaration and Programme of Action,
See A/CONF.189/12 and A/CONF.189/12/Corr.1, chap. I. including the provisions on multiple or aggravated forms of discrimination;

Takes note of the report of the Secretary-General on the effective promotion of the Declaration
A/80/288. and the reports of the Special Rapporteur on minority issues;
A/79/169 and A/80/186.
